    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Nádasdy (Augsburg, 18 November 1550)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. To his knowledge, the plague is ravaging Vienna, so
                            they should look for a safer place for his sisters and nephews. He asks
                            Nádasdy to help his family find a place if the need arises. 2. As for
                            the late Ferenc Frangepán’s bishopric, he has already written about it
                            to Nádasdy, he is waiting for an answer as to whether he should make
                            plans for taking that seat. They are expecting Maximilian from Spain,
                            King Ferdinand I and Queen Mary are expected to be arriving after
                            him.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Servitiorum meorum commendationem, Spectabilis et Magnifice Domine
                    et Amice Observandissime!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Intelligimus <placeName>Viennae</placeName> pestem coepisse
                    grassari, quid si ita est, quaerendus est nobis aliquis locus salubris, ad quem
                    sorores nostrae et nepotes<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Oláh’s sisters,
                        nephews, and nieces lived in Oláh’s Vienna palace, see Ep.
                            736.<ref>olahus.tei.15500323_1</ref></note> usque ad reditum nostrum
                    commigrare possint. Rogamus itaque Dominationem Vestram, uti dominum et fratrem,
                    ut si pestis <choice>
                        <orig>Vien<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>Vien<corr>nae</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> saevire coeperit, et necessitas fore videbitur, velit aliquem <choice>
                        <orig>loc<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>t</orig>
                        <supplied>loc<corr>um au</corr>t</supplied>
                    </choice> habitationem in bonis suis alicubi praemissae familiae <choice>
                        <orig>nos<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/>d</orig>
                        <supplied>nos<corr>trae a</corr>d</supplied>
                    </choice> tempus aliquot dare, ubi commorari et pestem, si Deo <choice>
                        <orig>pla<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>pla<corr>citum</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> erit, vitare possint, faciet in hoc Dominatio Vestra Magnifica rem
                    nobis gratam, quam eidem reservire volumus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] De rebus illis pontificalibus, quas quondam dominus
                        <persName>Colocensis</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Ferenc
                        Frangepán died in 1543, the Archdiocese of Kalocsa had been unfilled since
                        then.</note> testamento suo <del corresp="Olahus">canit</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">legavit</add> et de quibus nuper Dominationi
                    Vestrae Magnificae scripseramus,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">We do not
                        know this letter.</note> et <choice>
                        <orig>nunctiaveramus</orig>
                        <supplied>nuntiaveramus</supplied>
                    </choice>, cupimus habere responsum, ut sciamus nos praeparare ad officia nostra
                    peragenda. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Hic nihil novi est, de quo scribere possemus, nisi quod terimus
                    tempus inutiliter, magno taedio et expensis nescimus quarum rerum privatarum,
                    non dicimus regiarum, sed aliorum <choice>
                        <orig>g<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>g<corr>ratia</corr></supplied>
                    </choice>. Serenissimum regem <persName>Maximilianum</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Future Maximilian II, Holy Roman Emperor was
                            <hi rend="italic">designatus rex</hi> since 1549. He lived in the
                        Spanish court since 1548.</note> ex <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >Hispanias</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Hispaniis</add> huc <choice>
                        <orig>ventur<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>ventur<corr>um</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> exspectamus, et fortasse aliquo post tempore etiam <persName>principem
                        Ferdinandum</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.5">Ferdinand II,
                        Archduke of Austria.</note> atque <persName>Mariam</persName> reginam, rumor
                    enim de his inter multos vagatur. Quod reliquum est, Dominationem Vestram
                    Magnificam unacum domina <persName>coniuge</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.6">Orsolya Kanizsai.</note> sua carissima, domina nostra
                    observandissima feliciter valere optamus, quibus nos et servitia nostra
                    commendamus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Ex <placeName>Augusta</placeName> decima octavo Novembris anno
                    Domini 1550.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.6">
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Servitor et frater Agriensis etc. manu
                            propria.</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.7">Spectabili et magnifico domino Thomae de Nadasd comiti perpetuo
                    terrae Fogaras iudici curiae et consiliario regiae maiestatis ac supremo regni
                    Hungariae capitaneo etc. domino et amico nobis observandissimo.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
